                            <comment id="13247101" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2012 09:07:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you provide more details?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The timer consumer will cancel the task, when the consumer is suspended or stopped&lt;br/&gt;
and therefore the timer tasks stops firing. This is the expected behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13247295" author="gordonkl" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2012 15:35:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple test case which has a route started by a timer every second and just logs a message.  After running a time or two, we suspend the CamelContext and wait as we observe the timer continues to fire and the route executes despite being suspended.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13247372" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2012 17:01:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah thanks, we needed some logic in TimerConsumer to detect the suspend/resume.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13247375" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2012 17:06:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
